The '''Indian Hemp Decree''' (or the '''Indian Hemp Act''') was enacted in Nigeria on 31 March 1966 by Major General [[Aguiyi Ironsi]].<ref name="Kalunta-Crumpton2016">{{cite book|author=Anita Kalunta-Crumpton|title=Pan-African Issues in Drugs and Drug Control: An International Perspective|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KQirCwAAQBAJ&pg=PA126|date=3 March 2016|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-317-08434-1|pages=126–}}</ref> The act was preceded by the [[Dangerous Drug Ordinance]] of 1935, which restricted [[opium]] and other drugs.<ref name="Mou2016">{{cite book|author=Dr. Dan Mou|title=National Security, Democracy, & Good Governance in Post-Military Rule Nigeria, Volume One|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=l_8YDgAAQBAJ&pg=PT253|date=30 December 2016|publisher=AuthorHouse|isbn=978-1-5246-6801-3|pages=253–}}</ref>

