{{Politics of North Korea}}

'''Political parties in North Korea''' are heavily tied to the function of the government. [[North Korea]] has several parties, but the [[Workers' Party of Korea]] (WPK) has a stranglehold on political power.

As of the latest [[North Korean parliamentary election, 2014|election in 2014]], three parties (WPK, [[Korean Social Democratic Party]], and [[Chondoist Chongu Party]]) and one organization ([[Chongryon]]) are represented in the [[Supreme People's Assembly]], the country's parliament.

